From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 19:17:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Cix DSP memory mapping

Map vdev0buffer and vrings in addr_init so da_to_va works.
This allows the host to access rpmsg buffers and receive
Name Service announcements.
---
 drivers/remoteproc/cix_dsp_rproc.c | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/remoteproc/cix_dsp_rproc.c b/drivers/remoteproc/cix_dsp_rproc.c
index eb4d220f9961..022a4aa57f5e 100644
--- a/drivers/remoteproc/cix_dsp_rproc.c
+++ b/drivers/remoteproc/cix_dsp_rproc.c
@@ -599,11 +599,6 @@ static int cix_dsp_rproc_addr_init(struct cix_dsp_rproc *rproc_priv)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
 	for (i = 0; i < CIX_MEM_REG_NUM; i++) {
-		if (!strcmp(mem_reg[i].name, "vdev0buffer") ||
-		    !strcmp(mem_reg[i].name, "vdev0vring0") ||
-		    !strcmp(mem_reg[i].name, "vdev0vring1"))
-			continue;
-
 		p_mem[i].cpu_addr = devm_ioremap_wc(dev, mem_reg[i].sa, mem_reg[i].len);
 		if (!p_mem[i].cpu_addr) {
 			dev_err(dev, "failed to remap %#x bytes from %#llx\n",
